Creating a DOM element always follows this pattern:

🔑 The Golden 4 Steps
Create the element
Add content / attributes
Select parent
Attach (append) to DOM

createElement Syntax
document.createElement(tagName)

example:
<body>
  <div id="container"></div>
</body>

// 1️⃣ Create element
const para = document.createElement("p");

// 2️⃣ Add content
para.textContent = "Hello from JavaScript";

// 3️⃣ Select parent
const container = document.getElementById("container");

// 4️⃣ Attach to DOM
container.appendChild(para);
